22 silver bullion to the extent such gain is included in federal adjusted
23 gross income except that such gain shall not be subtracted if the gain is
24 derived from the sale of bullion as a taxable distribution from any
25 retirement plan account that holds gold or silver bullion. For the
26 purposes of this subsection, bullion has the same meaning as in section
27 77-2704.66.
